{"author":{"id":"243694e9f077d3ac0c74e4427a4b078da1cbfccfc08e2dea4e712b132f8f036e"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1659754324,"metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOARWYbc5H82Cj","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/188#issuecomment-1207132323"},"nonce":"oEvh/R7ohSZjFTDx2106cbXJXWY=","message":"I found the problem. The hashes use the global `ltc_state`, meaning they are not thread-safe. When tested on one thread, the bad seeds go away, at least for the first `0x15ffffff` seeds of sha-256. I don't know why this doesn't affect blake2 or sha-3 even though they have the same problem.","files":null}]}